  "modName": "Clearer Cities",
  "summary": "A small mod that reduces on the excessive snowstorms and fog in certain cities",
  "descriptionHtml": "I didn&#39;t like how the uneven weather some cities of Skyrim had. Riften and Falkreath, two of the only cities located in the middle of dense beautiful forests, yet the scenery is hampered by constant fog for most days. \r<br />There also seemed to be far too excessive snowstorms occurring in the cities located in colder regions. Too much so, it&#39;s kinda absurd how Windhelm isn&#39;t flooded in snow with how frequent blizzards would keep raining down on the city. Using the mod, Wet and Cold, made this especially annoying, which caused NPCs to stay indoors most of the time.\r<br />\r<br />This mod aims to remedy that by balancing on the weather occurences; making foggy weather and snowstorms less frequent in cities. \r<br />You can now appreciate the true beauty of cities and the surrounding nature like they are meant to be. Yay.\r<br />Their chances of occurences are balanced equally to the clearer days, so you will get more of an even scale of both good and bad weather. ",
